column1: [{"classname": "banded", "wiki": "A strip of material used for strengthening or coupling."}, {"classname": "blotchy", "wiki": "Covered in blotches."}, {"classname": "braided", "wiki": "To make a sudden movement with, to jerk."}, {"classname": "bubbly", "wiki": "Full of bubbles."}, {"classname": "bumpy", "wiki": "rough; jumpy; causing or characterized by jolts and irregular movements"}, {"classname": "chequered", "wiki": "The edible fruit of the wild service tree, Sorbus torminalis."}, {"classname": "cobwebbed", "wiki": "Covered with cobwebs"}, {"classname": "cracked", "wiki": "To form cracks."}, {"classname": "crosshatched", "wiki": "A pattern of crossing lines."}, {"classname": "crystalline", "wiki": "Of, relating to, or composed of crystals."}, {"classname": "dotted", "wiki": "A small, round spot."}, {"classname": "fibrous", "wiki": "Of or pertaining to fibre."}, {"classname": "flecked", "wiki": "A flake"}, {"classname": "freckled", "wiki": "A small brownish or reddish pigmentation spot on the surface of the skin."}, {"classname": "frilly", "wiki": "Having frills; frilled."}, {"classname": "gauzy", "wiki": "Resembling gauze; light, thin, translucent."}, {"classname": "grid", "wiki": "A rectangular array of squares or rectangles of equal size, such as in a crossword puzzle."}, {"classname": "grooved", "wiki": "A long, narrow channel or depression; e.g., such a slot cut into a hard material to provide a location for an engineering component, a tyre groove, or a geological channel or depression."}, {"classname": "honeycombed", "wiki": "A structure of hexagonal cells made by bees primarily of wax, to hold their larvae and for storing the honey to feed the larvae and to feed themselves during winter."}, {"classname": "interlaced", "wiki": "A decorative element found especially in early medieval art"}, {"classname": "knitted", "wiki": "To turn thread or yarn into a piece of fabric by forming loops that are pulled through each other. This can be done by hand with needles or by machine."}, {"classname": "lacelike", "wiki": "Resembling lace."}, {"classname": "lined", "wiki": "A path through two or more points (compare \u2018segment\u2019); a continuous mark, including as made by a pen; any path, curved or straight."}, {"classname": "marbled", "wiki": "A metamorphic rock of crystalline limestone."}, {"classname": "matted", "wiki": "A flat piece of coarse material used for wiping one\u2019s feet, or as a decorative or protective floor covering."}, {"classname": "meshed", "wiki": "A structure made of connected strands of metal, fiber, or other flexible/ductile material, with evenly spaced openings between them."}, {"classname": "paisley", "wiki": "A motif of a swirling droplet."}, {"classname": "perforated", "wiki": "To pierce; to penetrate."}, {"classname": "pitted", "wiki": "A hole in the ground."}, {"classname": "pleated", "wiki": "A fold in the fabric of a garment, usually a skirt, as a part of the design of the garment, with the purpose of adding controlled fullness and freedom of movement, or taking up excess fabric. There are many types of pleats, differing in their construction and appearance."}, {"classname": "polka-dotted", "wiki": "Having a regular pattern of round dots (polka dots)."}, {"classname": "porous", "wiki": "Full of tiny pores that allow fluids or gasses to pass through."}, {"classname": "potholed", "wiki": "A shallow pit or other edged depression in a road's surface, especially when caused by erosion by weather or traffic."}, {"classname": "scaly", "wiki": "Covered or abounding with scales."}, {"classname": "smeared", "wiki": "To spread (a substance, especially one that colours or is dirty) across a surface by rubbing."}, {"classname": "spiralled", "wiki": "A curve that is the locus of a point that rotates about a fixed point while continuously increasing its distance from that point."}, {"classname": "sprinkled", "wiki": "To cause (a substance) to fall in fine drops (for a liquid substance) or small pieces (for a solid substance)."}, {"classname": "stained", "wiki": "A discoloured spot or area."}, {"classname": "stratified", "wiki": "To become separated out into distinct layers or strata."}, {"classname": "striped", "wiki": "A long region of a single colour in a repeating pattern of similar regions."}, {"classname": "studded", "wiki": "A male animal, especially a stud horse (stallion), kept for breeding."}, {"classname": "swirly", "wiki": "Having swirls; swirling."}, {"classname": "veined", "wiki": "A blood vessel that transports blood from the capillaries back to the heart."}, {"classname": "waffled", "wiki": "A flat pastry pressed with a grid pattern, often eaten hot with butter and/or honey or syrup."}, {"classname": "woven", "wiki": "To form something by passing lengths or strands of material over and under one another."}, {"classname": "wrinkled", "wiki": "A small furrow, ridge or crease in an otherwise smooth surface."}, {"classname": "zigzagged", "wiki": "a line or path that proceeds by sharp turns in alternating directions"}]
